snippet.textDisplay: Something strange with the Gujrat City surroundings and its culture which has historically been so romantic and violent as well. Heer/Ranjha is another romantic sad story from the region. Even Alexander came and conquered this area but never went further into India because his soldiers refused to go any further. I just remembered that my mother's cousin was in love and wanted to get married to this girl but his father completely refused and was angry about it. The cousin said that both of will go to the river and drown themselves. His father still refused. So, both went to the river but he jumped in and died while the girl came back.

Happy to see the ppl around different countries realized its worth and i ll recommend them to listen to "Nescafe Basement" another pakistani music gala with some raw yet exceptional talent. snippet.textDisplay:
This is what I perceived from this song mentioned above

As we know the story is that the Sohni used to travel across river Chenab each night to meet mahiwal, but one day that clay pot replaced with the one having unbaked clay by her sister-in-law,From <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TrPvQvbp3Cg> 

 I like to consider it this way that the Sohni became aware of this fact before her journey to cross the river or else at a stage from where she could safely returned it is this point from where the song starts

00:00 --02:03
Sohni insist on crossing the river and meet her beloved, but the unbaked claypot is unwilling to go with sohni and says to sohni that the condition of the river and night is not good and so sohni should not insist on crossing the river but Sohni is firm on going as she consider turning back as a disrespect and in her view her life has less value than the promise she had made to her beloved that she will come and so she decides that she will go at any cost

02:04-- 3:18

The clay pot tries to convince sohni to return back by clarifying and reiterating the fact that he is made of unbaked clay and hence is unable to make her cross the river and is bound to destroy in the middle and calls that this fact is obvious and everybody knows it and request sohni not be stubborn and return.

03:19--- 03:48

Sohni decides to continue and ask the pot to help


03:49 --- 04:43

Sohni along with the pot continue the journey and pass through the points from where now it will be impossible to return back and hence a fear comes in the heart of sohni and pot and the nature witnessing the event and with this mix feeling of fear and excitement of meeting with her beloved sohni continues her journey

04:44 --- 5:40

The journey continues with the positive hope as it seems that sohni and pot will be able to make it to the other end

05:40 ----  7:54

( the pot gets damaged a little) Sohni reassures pot that don’t lose heart and help her in crossing the river and says she is sure that she has to meet her beloved and so ask the pot to continue with her a little more also she clarifies that if the pot didn't continued with her a lover will be greeted with the corpse of his beloved and hence the pot hold it a liitle more. It seems that sohni is pained by the possibility of not be able to reach her beloved rather than the possibility of sinking

7:55--- 8:07
(The  pot cracks further) Sohni Starts sinking, the nature witness with pain and grief.

8:08 --- 11:14

Background for the events change the clay pot disappear and the river become life and the love become the new pot holding which sohni is going to meet her beloved which is supreme self or soul  or (Whatever such exists). and now holding the love pot sohni is crossing the sea of life and is finally reaching to her beloved the supreme.
The nature witness the ultimate and grand  meeting of a soul with a supreme soul.
